HEADWORD: Occasive
<hw>Oc*ca"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>occasivus</ets>, fr. <ets>occasus</ets> a going down, setting of
the heavenly bodies, fr. <ets>occidere</ets> to fall or down. See
<er>Occasion</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the setting sun;
falling; descending; western.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

